# ============================================================
# FLOCK MANAGEMENT APP – GLOBAL AGENT RULES
# ============================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. CORE PRINCIPLES
# ------------------------------------------------------------

- This is a production-grade Android application.
- Stability > Features.
- Never introduce breaking changes without explicit instruction.
- Never remove existing working functionality.
- Never refactor large architecture sections unless explicitly requested.
- Always preserve backward compatibility with Room migrations.
- Always assume the app has paying subscribers.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. ARCHITECTURE RULES
# ------------------------------------------------------------

- Architecture: MVVM + Clean Architecture.
- UI Layer: Activities / Fragments / Compose only.
- Business logic MUST live in ViewModel or UseCase.
- No business logic inside Activities.
- No direct database calls from UI.
- Repository is the only access point to data sources.
- Data flow must be unidirectional.

Layers:
UI → ViewModel → UseCase → Repository → DataSource (Room / Firebase / Billing)

Never bypass layers.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. THREADING RULES
# ------------------------------------------------------------

- All database operations MUST run on Dispatchers.IO.
- Never block the main thread.
- Use Coroutines only.
- No GlobalScope.
- ViewModelScope for UI logic.
- Repository handles suspend functions.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. ROOM DATABASE RULES
# ------------------------------------------------------------

- NEVER delete a column from an existing entity.
- NEVER rename a column without a proper Migration.
- ALWAYS increment database version when schema changes.
- ALWAYS provide explicit Migration object.
- fallbackToDestructiveMigration() is FORBIDDEN in release builds.
- Destructive migration allowed only if BuildConfig.DEBUG == true.

- All Entities must:
    - Have explicit primary key
    - Use @ColumnInfo for clarity
    - Avoid nullable unless logically required

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. BILLING & SUBSCRIPTIONS
# ------------------------------------------------------------

- Subscription logic must never be bypassed.
- Premium features must always check subscription state.
- No hardcoded “premium = true”.
- Billing logic must be isolated in BillingRepository.
- Ad display logic must respect subscription state.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 6. ERROR HANDLING
# ------------------------------------------------------------

- No silent failures.
- Always log errors with clear tag.
- Never swallow exceptions.
- Use Result wrapper or sealed class for state:
    Loading / Success / Error

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 7. UI RULES
# ------------------------------------------------------------

- UI must remain clean and modern.
- No business logic in XML.
- Avoid nested layouts when possible.
- Use ViewBinding or Compose.
- Maintain Light and Dark mode compatibility.
- Do not introduce inconsistent design patterns.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 8. FEATURE ADDITION RULES
# ------------------------------------------------------------

When adding a new feature:
1. Create data model
2. Add DAO
3. Add Repository method
4. Add UseCase if needed
5. Connect ViewModel
6. Connect UI
7. Add error state handling
8. Add migration if schema changed

Never shortcut steps.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 9. CODE QUALITY RULES
# ------------------------------------------------------------

- Kotlin only (no Java unless required).
- No unused imports.
- No duplicate logic.
- Avoid code duplication across modules.
- Prefer extension functions.
- Prefer sealed classes over enums when handling states.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 10. SAFETY GUARDRAILS
# ------------------------------------------------------------

- Never modify applicationId.
- Never modify signing configs.
- Never modify Play Billing product IDs.
- Never modify Firebase project configuration.
- Never remove analytics tracking without request.
- Never alter release build settings.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 11. TESTING REQUIREMENTS
# ------------------------------------------------------------

- Repository logic must be testable.
- Avoid Android dependencies in business layer.
- ViewModel logic should be unit test friendly.
- Use fake repository for testing.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 12. CRASH PREVENTION POLICY
# ------------------------------------------------------------

Before finalizing changes:
- Ensure no nullability crash.
- Ensure no migration crash.
- Ensure no infinite recomposition.
- Ensure no memory leaks.
- Ensure no blocking main thread.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 13. WHEN UNSURE
# ------------------------------------------------------------

If unclear:
- Ask for clarification.
- Do NOT guess architecture.
- Do NOT rewrite existing structure.

# ============================================================
# END OF RULES
# ============================================================
